static void ll_invalidatepage ( struct page *  vmpage,
unsigned long  offset 
) [static]

Implements Linux VM address_space::invalidatepage() method.

This method is called when the page is truncate from a file, either as a result of explicit truncate, or when inode is removed from memory (as a result of final iput(), umount, or memory pressure induced icache shrinking).

[0, offset] bytes of the page remain valid (this is for a case of not-page aligned truncate). Lustre leaves partially truncated page in the cache, relying on struct inode::i_size to limit further accesses.
